[SN]TITLE[SN]
Road reopens after multi-vehicle crash in Glasgow

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A main road in the Scotstoun area of Glasgow which was closed after a crash involving a number of vehicles has been reopened.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Dumbarton Road was closed earlier in both directions near Harland Street.
An Audi travelling westbound on Dumbarton Road is believed to have collided with a Mini which was turning out of Harland Street.
Three other cars and a bus were damaged. Four people were treated at the scene for minor injuries.
The section affected was from the Thornwood roundabout to Balmoral Street. Local diversions had been in place.
